​Romelu Lukaku has insisted that he doesn't mind where he plays for Manchester United, saying that just being on the pitch for the club is an 'honour' as Ole Gunnar Solskjaer deals with an attacking injury crisis. <br />
<br />
&quot;Left or right or up front, it doesn't matter to me. Playing for this club is an honour and I just try to do my best, whichever position I play in. If it is on the right then I will try to create chances, which I did against Liverpool, and <span style="color: red;">if it is up front then I will try to score goals</span>. At the end of the day, I just try and help my teammates out and try win matches.&quot;
